SHOPID-19

An arcade game based on COVID-19

I started this project three months ago when I got this idea. I was working on some other game before that was also based on coronavirus but I discovered a game called snakeybus which was fun to play with fun physics. Therefore I dumped the old idea and combined the Snakeybus's concept with the concept of social

distancing in a supermarket.

I started this project on 15 April.

I was already learning game development for about one and a half years before it so I had the conﬁdence to start a big project and ﬁnish it and publish the game.

The basic concept is the player will control one cart and as he will collect more groceries and stuff in the supermarket new carts will be added on behind the player. So, for example, a player can control up to 10 carts continuously. The player has to control the ﬁrst cart and rest of the carts will follow the path taken by the ﬁrst cart.

So First I made a train like a controller in which the shopping carts behind the player cart will follow the ﬁrst cart maintaining a certain distance behind the next one. This is done by storing position vectors every frame of the game resulting in an array of vector3 positions. The child carts follow this array of vector3s. The twist in this is the child carts also have to consider the velocity of the player cart. For example, if the ﬁrst cart has travelled a distance of 0.02 units in one frame then all the child carts should also move only 0.02 units or else it will create an inconsistency in carts and the carts will follow each other in an unequal distance.

The player can use the keyboard arrows to control the player cart.

I also had to make an abstract map just to test the game.

Prototype map

Once this was done I started to create enemies/NPCs in the game from which you have to maintain social distance. So ﬁrst I created a basic navigational ai so that the NPC can move around the market and should avoid each other. Then the next step was to make a sphere with the NPC as its centre and a certain radius in which if the player enters the player can get infected resulting in reducing of health. So I also had to make a health mechanism with a UI element indicating the remaining health of the player. The player can get infected more and more if he comes closer to the NPC.

I kept on working on the small details of the game like making the controls more responsive, more VFX and shaders so that the game is more immersive and a lot more fun to play. I also did some post-processing of the screen by using Unity's post-processing stack.

NPCs infection radius

The next feature was ﬂying in the game just like the buses can ﬂy in the game snakeybus. For this, I just had to apply force from the bottom of the rigid body if the ﬂy button is pressed. If I ﬂy, the array of vector3 position will also store the ﬂying height so the child

carts can also follow the player cart while ﬂying. The boost/ﬂying has to limit so I had to implement a boost amount and recharge mechanism which was done by using the same mechanics of the health bar but also recharging it with time.

So far we have playable physics now its time to dab

So far we have playable physics and a prototype abstract map. So the prototyping phase is ﬁnished

Now we will make a vertical slice of the game containing ﬁnal VFX and models which will remain the same in the ﬁnal published product. This vertical slice includes a lot of designing and a little bit of coding. Designing is quite underrated in terms of time taken and hard work in the real world. This has taken a lot of time during the development as it is really hard to make things look good. I am using blender for making 3dmodels. Unity

and blender can work seamlessly with each other. So it was easy to import models and attach the already made scripts to it. For colouring and texturing of the objects, I use a small 8 by 8 pixels image in which every pixel contains different colour. This colour palette is assigned to models. This whole process of using a small texture image can reduce the draw calls for rendering exponentially.

My plans for this project is extending the map more, make an upgrade shop where you can upgrade your cart, adding more types of NPCs etc.

And my most important future idea is multiplayer in which players can play with each other in a map and can break each other's trail just like a multiplayer snake game.
